.TH LOOTSHEET-ENTRY-EXPENSE 1 "Mar 2026" "LootSheet" "LootSheet Manual"
.SH NAME
lootsheet-entry-expense \\- Record a guided expense entry
.SH SYNOPSIS
lootsheet entry expense [flags]
.SH DESCRIPTION
LootSheet CLI

Usage:
  lootsheet entry expense --account CODE --amount AMOUNT --description TEXT [--paid-from CODE] [--date YYYY-MM-DD] [--memo TEXT]

Defaults:
  --paid-from  1000
  --date       today

Rules:
  --account must be an active expense account
  --paid-from must be an active asset or liability account

Examples:
  lootsheet entry expense --account 5100 --amount 2SP5CP --description "Restock arrows"
  lootsheet entry expense --account 5300 --paid-from 2100 --amount 8GP --description "Inn charged to tab"
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
--account=string
expense account code (required) (default: )
.TP
--amount=string
expense amount (required) (default: )
.TP
--date=string
entry date in YYYY-MM-DD (defaults to today) (default: )
.TP
--description=string
journal entry description (required) (default: )
.TP
-h, --help
help for expense
.TP
--memo=string
optional line memo (default: )
.TP
--paid-from=string
funding account code (default: 1000)
.SH SEE ALSO
lootsheet-entry(1)
